# React, Next.js & Tailwind Patterns

## React Components

- **Functional components** only; no class components.
- **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, events, browser APIs).
- **One component per file** for complex components; small related components can colocate.
- **Extract custom hooks** for reusable logic (`usePatient`, `useCases`); keep components presentational when possible.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – Server Component (default)
export default async function PatientList({ userPhone }: { userPhone: string }) {
  const patients = await getPatientsByUserPhone(supabase, userPhone);
  return <PatientTable patients={patients} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD – Client only when needed
'use client';
export function PatientForm() {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  // ...
}
```

## Shadcn UI & Tailwind

- **Shadcn primitives** in `components/ui/`; do not add business logic there.
- **Tailwind for styling**; use `cn()` for conditional classes.
- **Prefer Shadcn components** over custom HTML when equivalent exists (Button, Input, Card, Dialog, Select, Table).
- **No inline styles** for layout/spacing; use Tailwind classes.
- **CSS variables** for theming; avoid hardcoded colors in components.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<Button variant="default" className={cn('w-full', isActive && 'ring-2 ring-primary')}>
  Salvar
</Button>

// ❌ BAD – inline style, custom button when Shadcn exists
<button style={{ width: '100%' }} className="bg-blue-500">Salvar</button>
```

## Compound Components

Use compound pattern for flexible, composable UI when a component has related parts.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – Card.CardHeader, Card.CardContent
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Paciente</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>{children}</CardContent>
</Card>

// Pattern: export parent + subcomponents; children receive context via React.createContext if needed.
```

## Reutilização

- **Primitives** in `components/ui/`; **feature components** in `components/dashboard/` or `components/forms/`.
- **Compose** small pieces; avoid massive "god" components.
- **Props over duplication**; extract shared layout (e.g. `DashboardLayout`) once.

## Next.js Patterns

- **App Router**; route groups `(auth)`, `(dashboard)`.
- **Layouts** for shared structure; `loading.tsx` for Suspense; `error.tsx` for error boundary; `not-found.tsx` for 404.
- **Server Components** for data fetching; pass data as props to Client Components.
- **Server Actions** for mutations when appropriate; avoid API routes for simple CRUD.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – fetch in Server Component, pass down
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <ClientTable data={data} />;
}
```

## Tailwind & Theme (Shadcn)

- **Tokens** in `app/globals.css`: `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, etc.
- **Tailwind config** extends theme; reference CSS vars: `backgroundColor: 'hsl(var(--background))'`.
- **No new colors in components**; use semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`).
- **Dark mode** via `class` or `media` in `tailwind.config`; Shadcn uses `hsl(var(--...))` for automatic theming.
